articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Israeli military strikes killed at least 20 Palestinians across the Gaza Strip on Sunday, including a local journalist and a senior rescue service official, local health authorities said.
articles.title: Israeli strikes kill 20 in Gaza, including a journalist and rescue service official

articles.author: Hatem Khaled, Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: The father of nine children killed in an Israeli military strike in Gaza over the weekend remains in intensive care, said a doctor on Sunday at the hospital treating him.
articles.title: Father in intensive care after nine children killed in Israeli strike on Gaza

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Trump said his tariff policy was aimed at promoting the domestic manufacturing of tanks and technology products, not sneakers and T-shirts.
articles.title: Trump says US wants to make tanks, not T-shirts

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Fragments from a Russian drone triggered a fire and caused damage to an apartment building in the Ukrainian capital Kyiv early on Sunday, a senior Ukrainian official said.
articles.title: Russian drone fragments set Kyiv apartment building ablaze, official says

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Russia's defence ministry said on Monday that air defence systems had downed 96 Ukrainian drones, including six over Moscow region.
articles.title: Russia says it downs 96 Ukrainian drones, some Moscow airports halt flights

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Uganda's military has severed all military cooperation with Germany after it accused Berlin's ambassador to Kampala of involvement in "subversive activities" in the East African country, its spokesperson said.
articles.title: Uganda's military says it has severed ties with Germany over 'subversive activities' by ambassador

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Venezuela's ruling socialist party held its significant majority in the National Assembly in a Sunday election, winning nearly 83% of votes, the electoral authority said, in a contest marked by deep division among parties opposed to the government of President Nicolas Maduro.
articles.title: Venezuela ruling party keeps control of legislature amid opposition division

articles.description: Shareeduh McGee is fighting to keep the memory of her cousin George Floyd alive.
articles.title: Five years after George Floyd's murder, racial justice push continues

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A magnitude 5.7 earthquake struck Chile's Tarapaca region on Sunday, the European Mediterranean Seismological Centre (EMSC) said.
articles.title: Magnitude 5.7 earthquake strikes Chile, EMSC says

articles.author: Sabine Siebold
articles.description: Germany's Chief of Defence, Carsten Breuer, has ordered the German military to be fully equipped with weapons and other material by 2029, a document seen by Reuters on Sunday shows.
articles.title: German chief of defence orders swift expansion of warfare capabilities
